    {
      "query": "What is the probability that the sample proportion is less than 0.5, i.e., P(𝑝̂ < 0.5)?",
      "answer": "We know that the sampling distribution of 𝑝̂ is normally distributed (since n is large), with mean p = 0.6 and standard deviation 𝜎_𝑝̂ = 0.049. Consequently, P(𝑝̂ < 0.5) = P{(𝑝̂ − p) / 𝜎_𝑝̂ < (0.5 − p) / 𝜎_𝑝̂} = P{z < (0.5 − 0.6) / 0.049} = P(z < −2.04)."
